## Three-scenario test (production-grade standard)

**EVERY skill in this kit must pass this test before being marked production-ready.** Run all three scenarios. If any fails, the failure tells you exactly what instruction to add to the skill.

### Scenario 1 — Happy path

A normal, straightforward input that represents 80% of real use cases.

**Test input:** [describe the test input — specific, realistic, ready to paste]

**Expected output:** [describe what the AI should produce — specific, testable]

**Pass criteria:** [what makes this pass — output you'd be comfortable shipping to a real user]

### Scenario 2 — Edge case

A weird, unusual, or incomplete input that tests the boundaries. Missing data. Unusual formatting. Conflicting information.

**Test input:** [describe the edge case input]

**Expected output:** [describe what the AI should do — usually: handle gracefully, ask for clarification, or skip cleanly]

**Pass criteria:** [the AI doesn't crash, doesn't fabricate, doesn't silently drop data]

### Scenario 3 — Stress test

The biggest, messiest, most complex version of the task. Reveals whether the skill scales or only works on simple inputs.

**Test input:** [describe the stress test — large file, complex case, multiple branches, etc.]

**Expected output:** [describe what success looks like at scale]

**Pass criteria:** [output stays useful + correct under load; AI doesn't blur into generality]

### Marking production-grade

Add to this skill's frontmatter once all three scenarios pass:

```yaml
production_grade: true
last_qa: YYYY-MM-DD
```

Re-run the three-scenario test whenever the skill's instructions change meaningfully. Drop `production_grade: true` if a scenario regresses.

